{
  "texts": [
    "(9) are available in the supplementary materials (see Supplemental Section 2).",
    "The expected score is given as",
    "The expected importance metric of model i consists of two kinds of terms.",
    "The ESPE terms capture the accuracy of the individual models.",
    "The first term shows that the expected importance of model i is lower when that model has a large ESPE, while the second term shows it is lower when the combined ESPE of the other models is small."
  ]
}